Our panelists will also share some of their personal and professional experiences and advice.
Ori Lifestyle’s Afrocentric founder Titilolami Bello has always been passionate about raising awareness on how to care for natural hair and has been known to put together courses to raise awareness within her community.
Hers is a holistic approach which pays attention to key aspects of well-being such as nutrition, exercise, sleep and stress management.
Her co-convener Tolu Blooms runs Blooms Hair Atelier which is a healthy hair care salon based in Ikoyi, Lagos where they equally take a holistic approach to hair, helping customers treat, nurture and grow their natural hair, in line with their hair goals.
They offer a range of carefully curated treatments that are backed by science and trichology, to address the needs of natural hair. 